{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Design generative AI experiences that leverage the strengths of the Foundation Models framework. We’ll start by showing how to design prompts for the on-device large language model at the core of Apple Intelligence. Then, we’ll introduce key ideas around AI safety, and offer concrete strategies to make your generative AI features safe, reliable, and delightful."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Key Takeaways","anchor":"Key-Takeaways"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🤖 Best for simple tasks; no facts, math, and code generation","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✍️ Use clear prompts with commands, examples and length control"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ Multiple safety layers: built-in guardrails, instructions, and input controls"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"🧪 Evaluation and testing required for better quality and safety","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design for on-device LLM","anchor":"Design-for-on-device-LLM"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The on-device LLM has some limitations:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Complex tasks","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Break down tasks into simpler steps to get good results"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Math calculations"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use traditional (non-AI) code for calculations instead"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Code generation"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid code generation prompts since the model is not optimized for code"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Factual or world knowledge"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Don’t rely on the model for facts and recent events","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Can still be used in games and scenarios where the accuracy of the output is not too important","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hallucinations"}]}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use guided generation (see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-286-Meet-the-Foundation-Models-framework","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") to improve response reliability","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Hallucination example (model thinks plain bagels have toppings):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Bagel-Mistake","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Prompting best practices","anchor":"Prompting-best-practices"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use length qualifiers, such as paragraph or word count"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example phrases: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“in a few words”"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“in three sentences”","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“in a single paragraph”"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", “in detail”"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let prompt = \"In a single paragraph, generate a bedtime story about a fox.\""],"type":"codeListing"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specify a role and style"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Role-and-Style","type":"image"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use clear commands"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Give a single specific task in detail","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide up to 5 examples"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use all-caps strong commands like MUST and DO NOT to control the behavior","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Tip","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new Playgrounds feature (see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-247-Whats-new-in-Xcode","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") is a great place to test prompts directly in Xcode"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-248-Playground"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Instructions vs Prompts","anchor":"Instructions-vs-Prompts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The aforementioned best practices are applicable to both instructions and prompts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"instruction"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a special type of prompt that defines how the model should behave across all subsequent prompts in a session."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The model receives the instruction before any other prompt."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Instructions","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Interactive experiences","anchor":"Interactive-experiences"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can offer some interactivity in your app by allowing your users to provide prompts to the model."}]},{"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[],"size":1},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-248-Interactivity"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":2},{"content":[],"size":1}],"numberOfColumns":4},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design for safety","anchor":"Design-for-safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While Apple’s Foundation Models framework comes with integrated safety features, it’s important to evaluate potential risks specific to your app."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Built-in guardrails","anchor":"Built-in-guardrails"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The framework automatically applies guardrails to:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Input:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Instructions, prompts, and tool calls are screened for harmful content","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Output:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Model responses are filtered even if inputs bypass the initial screening"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can catch and handle guardrail violation errors:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["do {","    try await session.respond(to: prompt)","} catch LanguageModelSession.GenerationError.guardrailViolation {","    print(\"Safety guardrail violation occurred.\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Errors occurring in "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"proactive features"}]},{"type":"text","text":", not driven by user actions, are safe to ignore. However, any errors originating from "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"user-initiated features"}]},{"type":"text","text":" should show suitable UI feedback to the user."}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Build trust and safety","anchor":"Build-trust-and-safety"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disallow inappropriate content"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Handle user input with care","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Evaluate potential consequences of users acting on your app’s output"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Add safety instructions","anchor":"Add-safety-instructions"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[],"size":1},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Safety-Instructions","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":2},{"content":[],"size":1}],"numberOfColumns":4},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Instructions should only come from you as the developer. Never include untrusted user content in your instructions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"User input handling patterns","anchor":"User-input-handling-patterns"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Direct user input (high flexibility, high risk)"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let prompt = userInput"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Combined prompts (balanced approach)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let prompt = \"Generate a story about \\(userInput)\""],"syntax":"swift"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Curated prompts (low flexibility, low risk)"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["enum Topic: String {","    case adventure = \"an adventure in an ancient forest\"","    case fantasy = \"a fantasy on an uninhibited island\"","}","","let topic: Topic = .adventure","let prompt = \"Generate a story about \\(topic.rawValue)\""]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Use case-specific mitigations","anchor":"Use-case-specific-mitigations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider the real-world impact of the generated content in your app. Here are some examples:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Bagel flavor generation app","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Show an allergen warning","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the ability to disable some ingredients in app settings"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Trivia generation app"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use denying keywords in your instructions to avoid controversial political topics or inappropriate content"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Train a classifier for more reliable outputs","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Layering-based approach","anchor":"Layering-based-approach"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The aforementioned safety recommendations act as multiple layers. Each layer has its weaknesses but when stacked together, the chances of a safety violation passing through all of them is very low.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[]},{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Layers","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":1,"content":[]}],"numberOfColumns":3},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Evaluate and test","anchor":"Evaluate-and-test"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Curate a dataset with prompts for all use cases and safety issues","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create automated tests with manual checks"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use another LLM to grade responses","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Test failure scenarios with safety violations to see how your app behaves"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The model will be updated continuously. Make sure to report any safety issues you encounter."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Safety checklist","anchor":"Safety-checklist"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"checked":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Handle guardrail violation errors","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add safety instructions","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control user input in prompts"}]}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apply use case-specific mitigations"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Evaluate and test"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Written By","anchor":"Written-By"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"terlan98","type":"image"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"anchor":"Tarlan-Ismayilsoy","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Tarlan Ismayilsoy"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/"}]}]}],"numberOfColumns":5},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal Notice"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple."}]}]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (22 min)","isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/248"}},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Explore prompt design & safety for on-device foundation models","role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC25"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-248-explore-prompt-design-and-safety-for-ondevice-foundation-models"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"WWDC25-248-Role-and-Style":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Role-and-Style.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Role-and-Style","alt":null},"WWDC25-248-Interactivity":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-248-Interactivity","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Interactivity.png"}]},"https://github.com/terlan98":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98","type":"link","title":"GitHub","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98"},"WWDC25-248-Playground":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Playground.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Playground","alt":null},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/248":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/248","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/248","checksum":null},"WWDC25.jpg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"},"https://":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"title":"Blog","url":"https:\/\/"},"WWDC25-248-Layers":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Layers.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Layers","alt":null},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"terlan98":{"type":"image","identifier":"terlan98","alt":"Profile image of Tarlan Ismayilsoy","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","title":"WWDC Notes","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}]},"WWDC25-248-Bagel-Mistake":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Bagel-Mistake.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Bagel-Mistake","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","title":"WWDC25","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-247-Whats-new-in-Xcode":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the latest productivity and performance advancements in Xcode 26. Learn how to leverage large language models in your development workflow. Explore editing and debugging enhancements, improved performance and testing tools, and Swift Build - the open-source build system engine used by Xcode."}],"kind":"article","title":"What’s new in Xcode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-247-Whats-new-in-Xcode","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-247-whats-new-in-xcode"},"WWDC25-248-Safety-Instructions":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Safety-Instructions.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Safety-Instructions"},"terlan98.jpeg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","type":"image"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributions are welcome!"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Contributions are welcome!","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-286-Meet-the-Foundation-Models-framework":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to tap into the on-device large language model behind Apple Intelligence! This high-level overview covers everything from guided generation for generating Swift data structures and streaming for responsive experiences, to tool calling for integrating data sources and sessions for context management. This session has no prerequisites."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-286-meet-the-foundation-models-framework","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Meet the Foundation Models framework","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-286-Meet-the-Foundation-Models-framework"},"WWDC25-248-Instructions":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-248-Instructions.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC25-248-Instructions"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/terlan98":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS Developer"}],"images":[{"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"kind":"article","title":"Tarlan Ismayilsoy (2 notes)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/terlan98"}}}